ymptoms that could indicate the occurrence of torsade de pointes such as dizziness, palpitations, or syncope.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/172947/', '[1] "Product Information. Fareston (toremifene)." Schering Laboratories, Kenilworth, NJ.[2] "Product Information. Fareston (toremifene)." Schering Laboratories, Kenilworth, NJ.[3] Therapeutic Research Faculty "Natural Medicines Comprehensive Database. Available from: URL: http://www.naturaldatabase.com." ([1995-2008...]):[4] Wohlt PD, Zheng L, Gunderson S, Balzar SA, Johnson BD, Fish JT "Recommendations for the use of medications with continuous enteral nutrition." Am J Health Syst Pharm 66 (2009): 1438-67[5] "Product Information. VFEND (voriconazole)." Pfizer U.S. Pharmaceuticals, New York, NY.', 1767363026);
